    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Back up the database with Google Sheets and Google Drive without manual work\n\n**Pattern:** Backup & Archive · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nBack up the database with Google Sheets and Google Drive without manual work. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual data transforms is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Download from Google Drive → Parse CSV Contents → Clean & Reshape Rows → Load Rows into Google Sheets → Repack as XLSX → Archive Processed File (Google Drive) → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to backup & archive without manual effort\n- Anyone automating data transforms in software development\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "b0a81f32-fdb5-ea25-21ee-b90b04e2ab84",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your data transforms process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
